- This is more compact than fixed-length prefixes for strings of varying lengths

### Reading Function (`read_string_prefixed_varint`):
- Uses the `operator>>` overload for `prefixed_varint<std::string>` adaptor
- First decodes the variable-length integer prefix to determine the string length
- Then reads exactly that many bytes into the result string
- Returns the reconstructed string

